quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,139,"And they denied him, so We destroyed them. Indeed in that is a sign, but most of them were not to be believers."
  26,140,"And indeed, your Lord - He is the Exalted in Might, the Merciful."
  26,141,"Thamūd denied the messengers"
  28,85,"Indeed, [O Muḥammad], He who imposed upon you the Qur’ān will take you back to a place of return.{1} Say, ",footnotes:1:[Meaning to Makkah (in this life) or to Paradise (in the Hereafter).]
  28,86,"And you were not expecting that the Book would be conveyed to you, but [it is] a mercy from your Lord. So do not be an assistant to the disbelievers.{1}",footnotes:1:[In their religion by making any concessions to their beliefs.]
  28,87,"And never let them avert you from the verses of Allāh after they have been revealed to you. And invite [people] to your Lord. And never be of those who associate others with Allāh."
  29,52,"Say, "
  29,53,"And they urge you to hasten the punishment. And if not for [the decree of] a specified term, punishment would have reached them. But it will surely come to them suddenly while they perceive not."
  29,54,"They urge you to hasten the punishment. And indeed, Hell will be encompassing of the disbelievers"
  30,31,"[Adhere to it], turning in repentance to Him, and fear Him and establish prayer and do not be of those who associate others with Allāh"
  30,32,"[Or] of those who have divided their religion and become sects, every faction rejoicing in what it has.{1}",footnotes:1:[Of beliefs, opinions, customs, etc.]
  30,33,"And when adversity touches the people, they call upon their Lord, turning in repentance to Him. Then when He lets them taste mercy from Him, at once a party of them associate others with their Lord,"
  31,16,"[And Luqmān said], ",footnotes:1:[Refer to footnote of 6:103.]
  31,17,"O my son, establish prayer, enjoin what is right, forbid what is wrong, and be patient over what befalls you. Indeed, [all] that is of the matters [requiring] resolve.{1}",footnotes:1:[For the reason that they are enjoined by Allāh.]
  31,18,"And do not turn your cheek [in contempt] toward people{1} and do not walk through the earth exultantly. Indeed, Allāh does not like everyone self-deluded and boastful.",footnotes:1:[Rather, respect them by directing your face and attention to them.]
  32,1,"Alif, Lām, Meem.{1}",footnotes:1:[See footnote to 2:1.]
  32,2,"[This is] the revelation of the Book about which there is no doubt from the Lord of the worlds."
  32,3,"Or do they say, "